race.comment: ANCHOR DOWN (1) found the line well at Hamilton last time when firmly in the market to finish fourth and looks to be heading the right way, finding an ideal race here for the Danny O'Brien yard with good jockey Liam Riordan looking to set up well from a middle gate. TWINKLE VAN WINKLE (10) presents third up. Two runs back have been good, not having the best of luck last time at Kilmore. Tricky draw here but will be running on well. PLAY ON WORDS (3) doesn't win out of turn but was good at Wodonga last time and will roll forward with the 4kg claimer on. TRUE PROPHET (8) looks suited getting to this trip third up now and Teo Nugent is a good booking. ELLE MCFEARSOME (9) is a place hope.
